for something ♪</i>

64
00:03:54.465 --> 00:03:56.075
Until we get the DNA results.

65
00:03:56.200 --> 00:03:58.861
I'll run a database on violent
predators in the area.

66
00:03:58.986 --> 00:04:01.147
Better search beyond the metro.

67
00:04:01.314 --> 00:04:02.348
Absolutely.

68
00:04:02.473 --> 00:04:03.583
We should also take another look

69
00:04:03.708 --> 00:04:05.184
at that Munson Creek Falls attack.

70
00:04:05.309 --> 00:04:06.419
You'll be busy.

71
00:04:06.544 --> 00:04:08.121
I'll take the iPod down for prints.

72
00:04:08.246 --> 00:04:10.030
Back in a minute.

73
00:04:16.997 --> 00:04:18.416
Hoo!

74
00:04:18.582 --> 00:04:21.794
Sorry. Nick. Guess I should
have worn my airbag today.

75
00:04:33.854 --> 00:04:41.939
♪ â™ª

76
00:05:30.411 --> 00:05:32.121
We've got 23 known predators

77
00:05:32.246 --> 00:05:34.156
within five square Miles
of the crime scene.

78
00:05:34.281 --> 00:05:36.209
None of them rise
to the kind of violence we saw

79
00:05:36.334 --> 00:05:37.910
out there this morning.

80
00:05:38.035 --> 00:05:39.845
Just got a hit on a missing person.

81
00:05:39.970 --> 00:05:42.348
University student went out
jogging this morning

82
00:05:42.473 --> 00:05:45.378
and never came back.

83
00:05:47.094 --> 00:05:49.340
She left at 7:30 this morning.

84
00:05:49.506 --> 00:05:50.656
and I'm a little freaked out.

85
00:05:50.781 --> 00:05:52.558
because she's always back by 8:30.

86
00:05:52.683 --> 00:05:53.893
Do you have a photo of her?

87
00:05:54.018 --> 00:05:55.033
On my iPhone.

88
00:05:55.158 --> 00:05:57.263
Do you know what kind of
running shoes she was wearing?

89
00:05:57.388 --> 00:05:58.849
Uh. pink Nikes.

90
00:06:04.462 --> 00:06:06.565
Hard to believe that's
the girl we saw this morning.

91
00:06:06.731 --> 00:06:08.774
Sylvie Oster. positive I.D.

92
00:06:08.899 --> 00:06:10.610
Well. at least we know who she is.

93
00:06:10.735 --> 00:06:11.644
Man. what a way to go.

94
00:06:11.769 --> 00:06:13.679
Just hope it happened fast.

95
00:06:13.804 --> 00:06:15.157
Man. let's get the hell out of here.

96
00:06:15.323 --> 00:06:16.867
Yeah.
It's been a long day.

97
00:06:18.114 --> 00:06:19.537
Big night.

98
00:06:19.703 --> 00:06:21.789
Don't blow it. Romeo.

99
00:06:56.591 --> 00:06:57.592
Juliette?

100
00:07:13.965 --> 00:07:16.218
Aunt Marie.

101
00:07:16.384 --> 00:07:17.470
When did you get here?

102
00:07:17.636 --> 00:07:19.847
Hey. She was here when I got home.

103
00:07:20.013 --> 00:07:21.182
Sorry for the short notice.

104
00:07:21.348 --> 00:07:22.433
What. you didn't know she was coming?

105
00:07:22.599 --> 00:07:23.983
I meant to call.

106
00:07:24.108 --> 00:07:25.618
Sometimes I mean to do something.

107
00:07:25.743 --> 00:07:27.313
and I assume I usually have.

108
00:07:27.479 --> 00:07:28.773
Well. how are you doing?
Is everything okay?

109
00:07:28.939 --> 00:07:30.941
Not as okay as I used to be.

110
00:07:31.107 --> 00:07:32.274
She was telling me
some pretty funny stories

111
00:07:32.399 --> 00:07:33.611
about when you were little.

112
00:07:33.777 --> 00:07:34.820
Dead frog in the microwave?

113
00:07:34.986 --> 00:07:37.246
Among others.

114
00:07:37.371 --> 00:07:38.741
Come and give us a hug.

115
00:07:38.907 --> 00:07:40.493
Here.

116
00:07:42.492 --> 00:07:44.330
We need to talk.

117
00:07:49.735 --> 00:07:51.010
How bad is it?

118
00:07:51.135 --> 00:07:53.629
Two months. two weeks. two days.

119
00:07:53.754 --> 00:07:55.508
Nobody knows.

120
00:07:55.674 --> 00:07:58.634
But there are so many things
I have to tell you.

121
00:07:58.759 --> 00:08:00.586
Why didn't you come here sooner?

122
00:08:00.711 --> 00:08:03.105
- I couldn't.
- Why?

123
00:08:03.230 --> 00:08:06.392
Just listen to me.

124
00:08:06.517 --> 00:08:08.761
There are things you don't know.

125
00:08:08.886 --> 00:08:09.962
Things about your family.

126
00:08:10.087 --> 00:08:12.198
My family?

127
00:08:12.323 --> 00:08:13.526
You're my family.

128
00:08:13.692 --> 00:08:16.836
Have you been seeing strange things?

129
00:08:16.961 --> 00:08:19.198
Things that you can't explain?

130
00:08:22.492 --> 00:08:23.786
Oh. I knew it.

131
00:08:23.952 --> 00:08:25.978
This is all happening so much faster

132
00:08:26.103 --> 00:08:27.413
than I thought it would.

133
00:08:27.538 --> 00:08:29.448
When it happened to me.
it knocked me on my ass.

134
00:08:29.573 --> 00:08:30.876
I couldn't move for a week.

135
00:08:31.042 --> 00:08:32.378
What are you talking about?

136
00:08:32.544 --> 00:08:35.714
The misfortune of our family
is already passing to you.

137
00:08:35.880 --> 00:08:37.156
I'm so sorry.

138
00:08:37.281 --> 00:08:39.385
I know you love Juliette.

139
00:08:39.551 --> 00:08:42.346
but you have to end it
and never see her again.

140
00:08:42.512 --> 00:08:44.930
It's just too dangerous.

141
00:08:45.055 --> 00:08:46.689
What?

142
00:08:50.020 --> 00:08:52.071
Oh. my God.

143
00:08:52.196 --> 00:08:53.691
He's here.

144
00:08:53.857 --> 00:08:55.276
Who?

145
00:08:56.609 --> 00:08:57.510
Hulda.

146
00:09:51.932 --> 00:09:58.419
<font color="#3399FF">Sync and correction by Mlmlte</font>
<font color="#3399FF">www.addic7ed.com</font>

147
00:10:07.004 --> 00:10:09.225
- Did you kill him?
- Yes.

148
00:10:09.391 --> 00:10:11.185
I thought I'd lost him.

149
00:10:11.351 --> 00:10:13.812
They're after me.

150
00:10:15.512 --> 00:10:17.483
Never lose this.

151
00:10:20.068 --> 00:10:21.744
Guard it with your life.

152
00:10:21.869 --> 00:10:24.129
They'll be looking for it.

153
00:10:24.585 --> 00:10:25.586
Nick.

154
00:10:27.415 --> 00:10:29.249
your parents didn't die in a crash.

155
00:10:30.461 --> 00:10:31.622
They were killed.

156
00:10:36.235 --> 00:10:37.236
What?

157
00:10:45.009 --> 00:10:47.019
I didn't see what happened.

158
00:10:47.144 --> 00:10:49.355
I just heard gunshots and called 911.

159
00:10:49.480 --> 00:10:51.307
It happened so fast.

160
00:10:51.432 --> 00:10:54.061
He came out of nowhere.
He had that thing

161
00:10:54.227 --> 00:10:56.313
in his hand.
and he went right for her. Hank.

162
00:10:56.479 --> 00:10:59.066
- I had no choice.
- Take it easy.

163
00:10:59.232 --> 00:11:01.360
Now. you go to the hospital.
I'll handle this.

164
00:11:01.526 --> 00:11:03.319
She said she knew him.

165
00:11:03.486 --> 00:11:04.697
and his name was Hulda.

166
00:11:05.363 --> 00:11:06.863
I'll run his prints.

167
00:11:08.666 --> 00:11:10.108
You want me to come with you?

168
00:11:10.233 --> 00:11:11.710
No.

169
00:11:11.835 --> 00:11:13.579
I'll be home as soon as I can.

170
00:11:13.704 --> 00:11:15.406
Okay.
Love you.

171
00:11:30.847 --> 00:11:32.391
Mr. Burkhardt?

172
00:11:33.850 --> 00:11:35.352
She's conscious now.

173
00:11:47.071 --> 00:11:50.049
You saw him. didn't you?

174
00:11:50.174 --> 00:11:51.994
You saw who Hulda really was.

175
00:11:52.160 --> 00:11:53.537
I don't know what I saw

176
00:11:53.703 --> 00:11:55.554
or how you did that.

177
00:11:55.679 --> 00:11:56.689
What's going on?

178
00:11:56.814 --> 00:11:58.324
We have the ability to see

179
00:11:58.449 --> 00:12:00.426
what no one else can.

180
00:12:00.551 --> 00:12:01.961
When they lose control.

181
00:12:02.086 --> 00:12:03.929
they can't hide. and we see them

182
00:12:04.054 --> 00:12:05.424
for what they really are.

183
00:12:05.590 --> 00:12:08.052
Look. you need some rest.

184
00:12:08.218 --> 00:12:09.902
This is no fairy tale.

185
00:12:10.027 --> 00:12:12.222
The stories are real.

186
00:12:12.388 --> 00:12:15.392
What they wrote about
really happened.

187
00:12:15.558 --> 00:12:18.811
You are one of the last Grimms.

188
00:12:18.978 --> 00:12:21.398
I know it's a lot.

189
00:12:21.564 --> 00:12:23.315
and I wish I had more time.

190
00:12:23.440 --> 00:12:24.818
but everything's in my trailer.

191
00:12:24.984 --> 00:12:27.319
Sweetie. there's so much
you still don't know.

192
00:12:27.444 --> 00:12:29.573
Look. what you said
about my parents...

193
00:12:29.739 --> 00:12:32.191
You're vulnerable now.

194
00:12:32.316 --> 00:12:34.893
You need to be careful.

195
00:12:35.018 --> 00:12:37.396
Don't ever lose what I gave to you.

196
00:12:37.521 --> 00:12:39.748
I'm sorry. Mr. Burkhardt.

197
00:12:39.873 --> 00:12:42.892
You can see her again tomorrow.

198
00:13:26.603 --> 00:13:28.257
Hey. Nick.

199
00:13:28.423 --> 00:13:30.134
You get that translated?

200
00:13:30.300 --> 00:13:32.618
Yeah.

201
00:13:32.743 --> 00:13:35.639
It means "Reapers of the Grimms."

202
00:13:35.805 --> 00:13:38.390
That fits your buddy Hulda.

203
00:13:38.515 --> 00:13:40.561
Wait till you hear what I got on him.

204
00:13:42.395 --> 00:13:44.530
Hulda was from Boise. Idaho.
where he worked

205
00:13:44.655 --> 00:13:46.648
as an accountant.
but his prints came back

206
00:13:46.773 --> 00:13:48.500
as a Mr. Lindon from Chicago.

207
00:13:48.625 --> 00:13:50.402
wanted for assault. rape. and murder.

208
00:13:50.527 --> 00:13:52.371
But there's also warrants
matching those prints

209
00:13:52.496 --> 00:13:54.323
in Florida and Alabama.

210
00:13:54.448 --> 00:13:56.809
He was wanted
for assault. rape. and murder?

211
00:13:56.934 --> 00:13:58.210
Don't let the comb-over throw you.

212
00:13:58.335 --> 00:13:59.495
This was a bad guy.

213
00:13:59.620 --> 00:14:02.297
Hey. Nick. Captain wants to see you.

214
00:14:03.722 --> 00:14:04.710
What's he want?

215
00:14:05.605 --> 00:14:07.205
Guess you'll find out.

216
00:14:09.063 --> 00:14:12.613
If you had to shoot somebody.
you sure picked the right guy.

217
00:14:12.916 --> 00:14:14.595
How you doing?
You holding up?

218
00:14:15.665 --> 00:14:16.513
Yes. sir.

219
00:14:17.091 --> 00:14:18.897
A first shooting is no small thing.

220
00:14:19.022 --> 00:14:20.976
You'll be required to see
the police psychologist.

221
00:14:22.101 --> 00:14:23.102
Yes. sir.

222
00:14:24.368 --> 00:14:25.718
Make sure you do.

223
00:14:26.625 --> 00:14:27.825
Get some rest.

224
00:16:28.603 --> 00:16:30.105
How long have you been down here?

225
00:16:30.271 --> 00:16:32.107
I couldn't sleep.

226
00:16:32.273 --> 00:16:33.775
What is all this?

227
00:16:33.941 --> 00:16:35.193
I don't know.

228
00:16:35.359 --> 00:16:38.537
I'll deal with it later.

229
00:16:38.662 --> 00:16:41.783
I'm sorry.
Let's go back to bed.

230
00:16:45.602 --> 00:16:47.512
How long did you live with Marie?

231
00:16:47.637 --> 00:16:49.748
She was my mother
from the time I was 12.

232
00:16:49.873 --> 00:16:51.750
- After your parents died?
- Yeah.

233
00:16:51.875 --> 00:16:54.296
You didn't live
in that trailer. did you?

234
00:16:54.544 --> 00:16:55.714
I didn't know she had it.

235
00:17:02.178 --> 00:17:04.153
I think it was just a cat.

236
00:17:09.626 --> 00:17:12.194
Yeah.

237
00:17:21.306 --> 00:17:22.864
This is what we're looking for.

238
00:17:22.989 --> 00:17:24.916
If this is an exact match
of the boot prints.

239
00:17:25.041 --> 00:17:26.417
it's going to be very helpful.

240
00:17:26.542 --> 00:17:27.768
Thanks.

241
00:17:27.893 --> 00:17:29.203
Take a look at the lab report.

242
00:17:29.328 --> 00:17:31.305
DNA of the attacker is inconclusive.

243
00:17:31.430 --> 00:17:33.085
Still don't know if we're
looking for a man or a beast.

244
00:17:33.251 --> 00:17:34.809
Well. we got a lead
if it wears boots.

245
00:17:34.934 --> 00:17:36.427
Based on the plaster cast.
this is the boot

246
00:17:36.552 --> 00:17:37.631
we're looking for.

247
00:18:07.535 --> 00:18:10.261
She's in a deep coma.

248
00:18:10.386 --> 00:18:12.430
There was a sudden spike
in the EKG this morning.

249
00:18:12.555 --> 00:18:15.755
but I don't have anything
definitive to tell you yet.

250
00:18:16.342 --> 00:18:17.754
Will she come out of this?

251
00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:19.965
Well. all we can do is wait.

252
00:18:20.131 --> 00:18:22.523
Did you know about the scars?

253
00:18:22.648 --> 00:18:24.177
What scars?

254
00:18:24.343 --> 00:18:26.827
A lot of them look like knife wounds.

255
00:18:26.952 --> 00:18:29.297
They're all over her body.

256
00:18:29.422 --> 00:18:31.616
What line of work was she in?

257
00:18:31.741 --> 00:18:33.645
She was a librarian.

258
00:18:36.729 --> 00:18:38.940
Yeah.

259
00:18:39.065 --> 00:18:41.065
On my way.

260
00:18:44.572 --> 00:18:46.280
Yeah. dispater. show 21.

261
00:18:46.405 --> 00:18:48.744
We're on scene.
and we're gathering evidence...

262
00:18:50.342 --> 00:18:51.836
I don't understand.

263
00:18:51.961 --> 00:18:54.388
She was supposed to go
straight there from school.

264
00:18:54.513 --> 00:18:55.489
Yeah. she never showed up.

265
00:18:55.614 --> 00:18:56.490
I looked all over the neighborhood.

266
00:18:56.615 --> 00:18:57.758
Then I came right here.

267
00:18:57.883 --> 00:19:00.338
Will you take care of that. please?

268
00:19:03.289 --> 00:19:04.732
- What do we know?
- Little girl

269
00:19:04.857 --> 00:19:05.933
on the way
to her grandfather's house.

270
00:19:06.058 --> 00:19:07.101
Never showed up.

271
00:19:07.226 --> 00:19:08.346
That's him. the guy with the beard.

272
00:19:08.512 --> 00:19:09.437
Do we know he's clean?

273
00:19:09.562 --> 00:19:11.266
No.
We're looking into that.

274
00:19:12.674 --> 00:19:14.144
That's the best photo they had.

275
00:19:16.280 --> 00:19:17.712
We don't know what we got here.

276
00:19:17.837 --> 00:19:20.692
relative. ransom. or pedophile.
and the clock is ticking.

277
00:19:20.858 --> 00:19:22.083
We're gonna split into teams.

278
00:19:22.208 --> 00:19:23.820
section off the paths she
would have taken from school.

279
00:19:23.986 --> 00:19:27.254
Now. it's a mile and a half
from the school to the house.

280
00:19:27.379 --> 00:19:29.757
When last seen. she was wearing
purple leggings

281
00:19:29.882 --> 00:19:31.325
and a red sweatshirt.

282
00:19:31.450 --> 00:19:34.122
Make sure you have a copy
of the photo and the map.

283
00:19:34.288 --> 00:19:36.541
You all know your sections.
so let's get out there and find her.

284
00:19:42.755 --> 00:19:44.021
- Captain.
- Yeah.

285
00:19:44.146 --> 00:19:45.806
When the university student
was attacked.

286
00:19:45.931 --> 00:19:47.385
she was wearing a red sweatshirt.

287
00:19:47.551 --> 00:19:48.762
The girl that was torn to pieces?

288
00:19:48.928 --> 00:19:50.711
Yeah.

289
00:19:50.836 --> 00:19:53.336
Well. let's hope
it's not the same guy.

290
00:20:02.081 --> 00:20:04.325
She's supposed to cross
Hunter Lane right there

291
00:20:04.450 --> 00:20:06.544
and then go around the park
to Hildebrand.

292
00:20:06.669 --> 00:20:08.379
The old man's house is
on the other side of the park.

293
00:20:08.504 --> 00:20:11.565
- Right?
- Right. 4753 Hildebrand Road.

294
00:20:11.690 --> 00:20:13.551
- Directly across from here.
- When I was a kid.

295
00:20:13.676 --> 00:20:15.497
I wouldn't have gone
all the way around the park.

296
00:20:15.663 --> 00:20:17.165
Well. the mother was
very specific about the route.

297
00:20:17.331 --> 00:20:19.223
Yeah. right.
Kids always do

298
00:20:19.348 --> 00:20:21.753
what their moms tell them to do.
I know I did.

299
00:20:21.919 --> 00:20:24.297
Come on. Nick.

300
00:20:39.218 --> 00:20:40.885
I'll take this trail.

301
00:20:46.444 --> 00:20:48.960
<i>You need to be careful.</i>

302
00:20:54.702 --> 00:20:57.622
<i>You're vulnerable now.</i>

303
00:20:57.788 --> 00:21:00.041
<i>This isn't a fairy tale.</i>

304
00:21:08.883 --> 00:21:10.899
Nick. I got something here.

305
00:21:20.603 --> 00:21:22.230
Robin Howell.

306
00:21:22.396 --> 00:21:24.989
She must have been grabbed
somewhere in this area.

307
00:21:25.114 --> 00:21:26.443
Careful where you step.

308
00:21:26.609 --> 00:21:30.044
We got a crime scene
in Berkeley Park.

309
00:21:30.169 --> 00:21:31.712
Yeah. off Hildebrand.

310
00:21:31.837 --> 00:21:33.914
Hank. we got boot prints here.
same kind.

311
00:21:34.039 --> 00:21:35.619
He took her this way.

312
00:22:09.318 --> 00:22:11.446
Hank. I got him!

313
00:22:22.414 --> 00:22:25.390
Where is she?
Where is she?

314
00:22:35.574 --> 00:22:36.918
Look. I know she's in here somewhere.

315
00:22:37.043 --> 00:22:39.754
You got another place
to look. we'll look.

316
00:22:39.879 --> 00:22:42.714
but we've torn this place apart.

317
00:22:45.801 --> 00:22:46.815
What are we doing here?

318
00:22:46.981 --> 00:22:49.109
If she's not in there.
he's got her someplace else.

319
00:22:49.275 --> 00:22:52.320
What do you see in this guy we don't?

320
00:22:52.486 --> 00:22:53.905
He's got no priors.
He's clean.

321
00:22:54.071 --> 00:22:56.270
He fits the profile... he's a loner.

322
00:22:56.395 --> 00:22:57.742
he's never been married.
he lives across the street

323
00:22:57.908 --> 00:22:58.940
from a park.

324
00:22:59.065 --> 00:23:00.141
That's not going
to get him into a court

325
00:23:00.266 --> 00:23:03.401
unless he sues our ass.

326
00:25:02.471 --> 00:25:06.287
You shouldn't have come back.

327
00:25:07.621 --> 00:25:09.003
Okay. okay. okay.

328
00:25:09.128 --> 00:25:11.000
Lighten up.
I'm just making a point.

329
00:25:11.166 --> 00:25:12.710
Come on.

330
00:25:12.876 --> 00:25:14.295
Let's grab a brew.

331
00:25:14.461 --> 00:25:16.673
And. by the way.
you're paying for that window.

332
00:25:22.303 --> 00:25:24.151
You know.
I never seen one of you before.

333
00:25:24.276 --> 00:25:25.886
I heard about you guys all my life.

334
00:25:26.011 --> 00:25:29.490
Never thought I'd see one up close.

335
00:25:29.615 --> 00:25:30.791
A Grimm.

336
00:25:30.916 --> 00:25:32.516
Ha!
What do you know?

337
00:25:33.836 --> 00:25:35.662
- You know about me?
- Are you kidding?

338
00:25:35.787 --> 00:25:38.165
My folks used to tell me stories
about you guys.

339
00:25:38.290 --> 00:25:40.768
Scared the hell out of me
when I was a kid.

340
00:25:40.893 --> 00:25:43.408
How long you been at this?
You seem kind of new.

341
00:25:43.574 --> 00:25:45.326
Who are you?

342
00:25:45.492 --> 00:25:46.807
Wow. you are new at this.

343
00:25:46.932 --> 00:25:48.872
What. someone in your family
just die?

344
00:25:49.038 --> 00:25:50.248
My aunt's in a coma.

345
00:25:50.414 --> 00:25:52.713
Ahh. that explains it.

346
00:25:52.838 --> 00:25:54.085
What's her name?

347
00:25:54.251 --> 00:25:55.461
Marie Kesler.

348
00:25:57.081 --> 00:25:58.082
Oh. yeah.

349
00:25:59.144 --> 00:26:00.654
I heard of her.

350
00:26:00.779 --> 00:26:03.057
Look. I don't want
any more trouble. okay?

351
00:26:03.182 --> 00:26:04.358
I'm not that kind of Blutbad.

352
00:26:04.483 --> 00:26:06.761
I don't kill anymore.
I haven't in years.

353
00:26:06.886 --> 00:26:09.267
Wait.
What did you say you were?

354
00:26:09.433 --> 00:26:10.631
Blutbad.

355
00:26:10.756 --> 00:26:13.934
Vulgarized by your ancestors
as the big. bad wolf.

356
00:26:14.059 --> 00:26:15.273
What. did you just get the books
tonight?

357
00:26:15.439 --> 00:26:17.025
You know about the books?

358
00:26:17.191 --> 00:26:19.073
Of course I know about the books.

359
00:26:19.198 --> 00:26:20.820
We all know about the books.

360
00:26:20.986 --> 00:26:24.449
You people started profiling us
over 200 years ago.

361
00:26:24.615 --> 00:26:27.065
But. as you can see.
I'm not that big.

362
00:26:28.073 --> 00:26:29.746
and I am done with the bad thing.

363
00:26:29.912 --> 00:26:31.936
- Well. how do you...
- How do I stay good?

364
00:26:32.061 --> 00:26:33.654
Through a strict regimen

365
00:26:33.779 --> 00:26:35.523
of diet. drugs. and Pilates.

366
00:26:35.648 --> 00:26:37.391
I'm a reformed Blutbad.

367
00:26:37.516 --> 00:26:38.526
A Wieder Blutbad.

368
00:26:38.651 --> 00:26:39.881
It's a different church altogether.

369
00:26:40.047 --> 00:26:41.591
You guys go to church?

370
00:26:41.757 --> 00:26:42.897
Sure.

371
00:26:43.633 --> 00:26:44.634
Don't you?

372
00:26:49.278 --> 00:26:52.573
Then what she said
is really happening to me.

373
00:26:52.698 --> 00:26:54.520
I have to stop it.
How do I stop it?

374
00:26:54.686 --> 00:26:56.801
Stop it?
You can't stop it.

375
00:26:58.370 --> 00:27:01.694
It's who you are.

376
00:27:01.860 --> 00:27:03.167
So if you just got into this.

377
00:27:03.292 --> 00:27:05.823
you must be seeing
some pretty strange things.

378
00:27:05.989 --> 00:27:08.868
Yeah.
I am.

379
00:27:09.034 --> 00:27:10.954
I guess that's why you're here.

380
00:27:11.120 --> 00:27:13.748
No. I'm here
because of the little girl.

381
00:27:13.914 --> 00:27:17.710
- Still haven't found her yet?
- No. We haven't.

382
00:27:17.876 --> 00:27:20.296
- Ah. look at this.
- You know where she is.

383
00:27:20.462 --> 00:27:21.969
Of course I don't know where she is.

384
00:27:22.094 --> 00:27:24.592
Did I not just tell you
about my strict regimen?

385
00:27:24.758 --> 00:27:28.542
So how many of you Blutbads
are there?

386
00:27:28.667 --> 00:27:31.391
First off. the plural is Blutbaden.

387
00:27:31.557 --> 00:27:32.934
And I don't know.

388
00:27:33.100 --> 00:27:35.149
We don't socialize much.

389
00:27:35.274 --> 00:27:37.051
Bad things happen
when we get into a pack.

390
00:27:37.176 --> 00:27:38.439
Especially when we see red.

391
00:27:38.605 --> 00:27:40.441
So all those things
I've been seeing...

392
00:27:40.935 --> 00:27:42.110
We're not things.

393
00:27:43.402 --> 00:27:44.758
Look. I'm a clockmaker.
for God's sake.

394
00:27:44.883 --> 00:27:46.489
I don't go around
abducting little girls.

395
00:27:46.655 --> 00:27:48.574
Okay. then tonight in the backyard.

396
00:27:48.740 --> 00:27:50.130
you were marking your territory.

397
00:27:50.255 --> 00:27:52.203
I wasn't pissing
on my fence for kicks.

398
00:27:52.369 --> 00:27:55.836
Then there are more of you
around here.

399
00:27:55.961 --> 00:27:59.023
Look. you may not know where she is.

400
00:27:59.148 --> 00:28:01.129
but you've got a pretty good
idea who's got her.

401
00:28:01.295 --> 00:28:02.776
I don't bother the other Blutbaden.

402
00:28:02.901 --> 00:28:04.590
- they don't bother me.
- Guess what. pal?

403
00:28:04.756 --> 00:28:05.880
I'm not a Blutbaden.

404
00:28:06.005 --> 00:28:06.981
I'm a cop.

405
00:28:07.106 --> 00:28:08.616
And if you know who's got her.

406
00:28:08.741 --> 00:28:10.471
you had better tell me right now.

407
00:28:10.637 --> 00:28:12.015
Please don't threaten me.

408
00:28:12.181 --> 00:28:13.725
I want to know who's got her.

409
00:29:27.719 --> 00:29:30.843
Don't be afraid.

410
00:29:31.009 --> 00:29:32.800
Do you like it?

411
00:29:32.925 --> 00:29:34.472
It's all yours.

412
00:29:34.638 --> 00:29:36.474
I just want to go home.

413
00:29:36.640 --> 00:29:39.006
You are home.

414
00:29:39.131 --> 00:29:41.687
What do you say we hang this up?

415
00:30:10.396 --> 00:30:12.343
Do you want a chicken pot pie?

416
00:30:36.283 --> 00:30:38.286
I really think I should drive.

417
00:30:38.452 --> 00:30:40.413
No. I'm good.

418
00:30:40.579 --> 00:30:42.540
If this is the same Blutbad
that killed that woman

419
00:30:42.706 --> 00:30:43.847
- in the woods...
- Well. assuming he fed

420
00:30:43.972 --> 00:30:45.382
yesterday. he'll be good for a week.

421
00:30:45.507 --> 00:30:47.083
maybe ten days. tops.

422
00:30:47.208 --> 00:30:50.387
He'll just use the time
to fatten her up.

423
00:30:50.512 --> 00:30:52.967
Whoa.
I got a hit.

424
00:30:53.133 --> 00:30:54.343
We're close.

425
00:30:54.509 --> 00:30:55.636
Did you really smell him?

426
00:30:55.802 --> 00:30:58.306
Dude. you have no idea.

427
00:31:22.496 --> 00:31:26.947
Okay. this is as far as we drive.

428
00:31:33.822 --> 00:31:34.884
What. he's over there?

429
00:31:35.050 --> 00:31:37.762
Oh. he's real close.

430
00:31:37.928 --> 00:31:40.537
- What's that?
- Wolfsbane.

431
00:31:40.662 --> 00:31:42.850
- So he won't sense us.
- You're kidding me. right?

432
00:31:43.016 --> 00:31:45.332
Not if you want to stay alive.

433
00:31:49.981 --> 00:31:51.275
What are you doing?

434
00:31:51.441 --> 00:31:53.486
Well. you said he was over there.

435
00:31:53.652 --> 00:31:56.086
Why don't you just call him.
tell him you're coming?

436
00:31:56.211 --> 00:31:57.240
This way.

437
00:32:04.079 --> 00:32:07.667
Isn't this what the bridge is for?

438
00:32:23.138 --> 00:32:24.350
Sorry.

439
00:32:24.516 --> 00:32:27.066
Do I need something
like silver bullets?

440
00:32:28.043 --> 00:32:30.147
What are you. an idiot?

441
00:32:38.219 --> 00:32:39.156
That's his place.

442
00:32:47.414 --> 00:32:48.416
What's happening?

443
00:32:51.866 --> 00:32:53.921
I can't guarantee what'll happen
if I go any closer.

444
00:32:54.087 --> 00:32:56.215
It's too dangerous.

445
00:32:56.381 --> 00:32:59.182
I might be on your side.
I might be on his side.

446
00:32:59.307 --> 00:33:00.845
I might even go after the girl.

447
00:33:01.011 --> 00:33:02.085
I'm sorry.

448
00:33:02.210 --> 00:33:03.848
But there's nothing more I can do.

449
00:33:04.014 --> 00:33:08.603
I'm out of here.

450
00:33:17.092 --> 00:33:18.029
What?

451
00:33:18.195 --> 00:33:19.572
I found her.

452
00:33:46.921 --> 00:33:48.726
I want to go home.

453
00:33:48.892 --> 00:33:51.525
I told you. you are home.

454
00:34:00.635 --> 00:34:02.946
Where is he?

455
00:34:03.071 --> 00:34:04.533
He's in a house

456
00:34:04.699 --> 00:34:05.882
on the other side of the stream.

457
00:34:06.007 --> 00:34:08.079
But you have to put
some of this on first.

458
00:34:08.245 --> 00:34:10.373
What the hell are you doing?

459
00:34:10.539 --> 00:34:11.749
So he doesn't smell us.

460
00:34:11.915 --> 00:34:13.334
We're not hunting deer.

461
00:34:13.500 --> 00:34:15.759
Where's backup?

462
00:34:15.884 --> 00:34:17.505
You're the only one I called.

463
00:34:17.671 --> 00:34:19.298
- What?
- I already cried wolf once.

464
00:34:19.464 --> 00:34:21.132
You think they're gonna believe me?

465
00:34:21.257 --> 00:34:22.258
Come on.

466
00:34:30.732 --> 00:34:31.741
How'd you find this place?

467
00:34:31.866 --> 00:34:34.554
Uh. the boots.

468
00:34:35.236 --> 00:34:37.024
I couldn't sleep.

469
00:34:37.190 --> 00:34:38.732
started looking at addresses.
this is one of them.

470
00:34:38.857 --> 00:34:40.100
- What's his name?
- Who?

471
00:34:40.225 --> 00:34:41.918
The guy we're looking for.

472
00:34:42.043 --> 00:34:44.421
I forgot.

473
00:34:47.148 --> 00:34:49.025
You do know there's a bridge. right?

474
00:34:49.150 --> 00:34:50.263
Man.

475
00:34:51.753 --> 00:34:54.531
You better be right this time. buddy.
You saw his boot prints. right?

476
00:34:54.656 --> 00:34:55.832
Yeah.

477
00:34:55.957 --> 00:34:58.170
- Up there up by the house.
- The exact match?

478
00:34:58.336 --> 00:34:59.736
From what I could tell. yeah.

479
00:34:59.861 --> 00:35:03.175
- You run his plates?
- I'm still waiting.

480
00:35:03.341 --> 00:35:04.407
What's the matter?

481
00:35:04.532 --> 00:35:06.011
Do you not trust me?

482
00:35:06.177 --> 00:35:08.973
Okay. let's do this.

483
00:35:40.278 --> 00:35:41.655
Good evening.

484
00:35:41.780 --> 00:35:43.799
Can I help you?

485
00:35:47.853 --> 00:35:49.446
Sorry to disturb you. sir.

486
00:35:49.571 --> 00:35:52.049
I'm Detective Griffin.
This is Detective Burkhardt.

487
00:35:52.174 --> 00:35:53.267
Do you have a few minutes?

488
00:35:53.433 --> 00:35:54.952
Of course.

489
00:35:55.077 --> 00:35:56.145
Would you like to come in?

490
00:35:56.311 --> 00:35:57.646
That would be great.

491
00:36:06.071 --> 00:36:10.851
♪ ♪

492
00:36:10.976 --> 00:36:13.871
We can sit in here.

493
00:36:16.565 --> 00:36:18.042
Nice pillows.

494
00:36:18.208 --> 00:36:20.594
I did the needlepoint myself.

495
00:36:20.719 --> 00:36:22.630
Not that I tell everyone.

496
00:36:26.491 --> 00:36:28.468
Oh. pot pie's done.

497
00:36:28.593 --> 00:36:30.304
Just give me a moment.

498
00:36:30.470 --> 00:36:31.639
and then we can talk.

499
00:36:31.805 --> 00:36:33.464
Okay?

500
00:36:35.517 --> 00:36:39.730
- Are you kidding me?
- Hank. I really believe this is the right guy.

501
00:36:45.343 --> 00:36:48.612
Excuse me. sir?

502
00:36:51.483 --> 00:36:53.193
Sorry it's taking so long.

503
00:36:53.318 --> 00:36:56.789
but you know how delicate crusts are.

504
00:36:56.955 --> 00:36:58.207
What kind of work do you do?

505
00:36:58.373 --> 00:36:59.866
I work for the Government.

506
00:36:59.991 --> 00:37:01.126
Like you.

507
00:37:01.292 --> 00:37:03.254
I'm a postman.

508
00:37:03.420 --> 00:37:05.548
Not the most glamorous job.
but I like it.

509
00:37:05.714 --> 00:37:08.642
Where were you between the hours
of 2:00 and 4:00 today?

510
00:37:08.767 --> 00:37:09.843
On my route.

511
00:37:10.010 --> 00:37:11.720
I'd like to know
what this is all about.

512
00:37:11.886 --> 00:37:14.781
This little girl went missing today.

513
00:37:14.906 --> 00:37:16.225
That's awful.

514
00:37:16.391 --> 00:37:18.477
You don't think I had anything
to do with this. do you?

515
00:37:18.643 --> 00:37:21.105
We have to run down
every possibility.

516
00:37:21.271 --> 00:37:23.482
What possibility
could have led you to me?

517
00:37:23.648 --> 00:37:25.442
We're looking for a pair of boots.

518
00:37:25.608 --> 00:37:29.238
Feel free to look anywhere you want.

519
00:37:34.534 --> 00:37:35.502
If this guy had something to hide.

520
00:37:35.627 --> 00:37:36.803
he would have kicked us out.

521
00:37:36.928 --> 00:37:39.764
I'm leaving.
I want to keep my job.

522
00:37:44.402 --> 00:37:47.080
♪ ♪

523
00:37:47.205 --> 00:37:49.657
Anything else?

524
00:37:52.385 --> 00:37:53.654
No.
Thanks for your time.

525
00:37:53.779 --> 00:37:55.472
We'll see ourselves out.

526
00:38:03.063 --> 00:38:04.131
Hank. I'm sorry.

527
00:38:04.256 --> 00:38:06.567
- I really thought this time...
- Wait.

528
00:38:06.733 --> 00:38:08.861
The song.

529
00:38:09.027 --> 00:38:10.070
What song?

